author: THOMAS TRACY
title: Second suspect nabbed in Rutgers student's murder
text:
Second suspect in Rutgers University student’s murder arrested in the Dominican Republic Second suspect nabbed in Rutgers student's murder Fraynned Ramirez (l.) was picked up by U.S. Marshals in the Dominican Republic Tuesday, and Marcus Feliz was nabbed shortly after the April 2016 shooting. (Essex County Prosecutor) NEW YORK DAILY NEWS  51 AM 
Authorities have arrested a second man for the killing of a Rutgers University student last year. 
U.S. Marshals picked up Fraynned Ramirez, 26, in the Dominican Republic on Tuesday. 
He is expected to be extradited back to Essex County on Wednesday, where he will be charged in the murder of student Shani Patel, 21, officials said. 
Patel was shot to death at his off-campus apartment near the university’s Newark campus on April 10, 2016, during a robbery. 
Patel’s roommate, a 23-year-old graduate student, was injured but survived, officials said. 
Ramirez’s alleged accomplice, Marcus Feliz, 25, was arrested shortly after the shooting and was charged with murder, robbery and weapons charges. Join the Conversation:
